<h1>Classical Integrable Systems</h1>

<h2>Starts August '15</h2>

<p>The topics we hope to cover include: Liouville integrability, Lax representations, the Toda and Calogero-Moser models, integrable heirarchies, and inverse scattering methods.</p>

<p>We plan to discuss the relevant mathematics -- elements of symplectic geometry, the theory of Riemann surfaces and some Lie theory -- as and when we require them.</p>

<p>Each meeting will go on for an hour and a half. We meet every Saturday at 10:00 AM in Hall 123.</p>


